[normal]Frequency of inspections[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Inspection methodology[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Enforcement Action[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Inspectors lacking expertise[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Lack of information in inspection reports[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]1. How much time was spent in the home? 
[normal]2. How many inspectors? 
[normal]3. The name of the inspector 
[normal]4. The time of the inspection 
[normal]5. How many relatives were spoken with or involved in the inspection via a survey? 
[normal]6. Whether there is a registered manager in post? 
[normal]7. If so, the name and qualifications of the manager 
[normal]8. If none, to say so and give the reasons 
[normal]9. Plus provider’s plan to deal with the vacancy and appoint a new manager 
[normal]10. Which regulations were found to have been breached during the inspection? 
[normal]11. The specific powers being used to take enforcement action 
[normal]12. Plus the time-table for this 
[normal]13. Which regulations are still in breach from any previous inspections and reasons, if any, for any continued breach 
[normal]14. If so, what further enforcement action will be taken? 
[normal]15. The number of complaints received, what they were about and whether or not they have been resolved? 
[normal]16. Any safeguarding concerns and if so, what about? and to whom referred? 
[normal]17. Some detail about the staffing ratio in the home and 
[normal]18. Whether there are any stimulating activities
